   <p>In some cases we can have one letter directly on top of another, as a manuscript variant, rather than a correction. For this purpose we use another value of the <att>rend</att> attribute, called 'stacked'. 
       Here is an example from the second volume of: <ref target="https://archive.org/stream/fragmentahistori02mueluoft#page/4/mode/1up">Fragmenta Historicorum Graecorum</ref>. This is an encoding of an edition, not an inscription/papyrus, 
       and the interpretation of these stacked letters is rather unclear. The editor is giving a reference to a manuscript.</p>
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
        Κάδμο<hi rend="stacked">ο</hi>ν
    </egXML>
    
